                <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00 Tacoma/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-16T18:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 16, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. I expect to have the notice of the invitation of the three Presidents to the
                    conference published in the local press this evening. I have received nothing
                    from Managua regarding the date but a telegram from Tegucigalpa states that
                    President of Nicaragua desires conference on the 19th and that this date is
                    agreeable to the President of Honduras. I have accordingly asked the President
                    of Salvador for that date and he has accepted provided nothing serious occurs to
                    prevent. We shall leave this city by special train Friday morning and hope to
                    sleep on the <hi rend="italic">Tacoma</hi> that night.</p>
                <p>Above repeated to Legations at Tegucigalpa and Managua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
